  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison does not know what President Abraham Lincoln thinks of him, &quot;having heard no word of commendation from his lips, and received none from his pen.&quot; Garrison doubts that he has influence over the President. Nevertheless, Garrison is writing a letter to President Lincoln endorsing John Murray Forbes&apos;s high opinion of Governor John A. Andrew&apos;s qualifications for a cabinet post. Garrison regards the anti-slavery amendment to the Constitution as indispensable.</subfield>
